  "original_title": "2024 \u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dc3\u0dd4 \u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0 ISS \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d89\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dd6\u0daf\u0dcf\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Russia is ready to leave the ISS after 2024",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Russia will withdraw from the International Space Station (ISS) project along with Western countries after 2024, according to the new head of the country's space agency, Roscosmos, Yuri Borisov.",
        "However, Moscow intends to fulfill all its obligations to foreign partners as part of the ISS project. But after 2024 it has been decided to leave this position, Borisov said at a meeting in the Kremlin.",
        "\"I think, by then we will start creating a Russian orbital space station,\" the Russian space chief added.",
        "In Borisov's view, Russia's manned space flights should be part of a systematic scientific program, so that each mission brings new knowledge to the country."
      ],
